# Customize TFE Toolbar Emojis

This guide shows how to change the toolbar buttons that appear at the top of TFE.

## Current Toolbar (as of v1.0.0)

```
[🏠] home  [⭐] favorites  [>_] command  [🔍] fuzzy search
```

## Location: view.go

Find the toolbar rendering code in `view.go` (around line 80-100):

```go
// Toolbar buttons
toolbar := lipgloss.JoinHorizontal(
    lipgloss.Top,
    buttonStyle.Render("[🏠] home"),
    " ",
    favoriteButton,
    " ",
    buttonStyle.Render("[>_] command"),
    " ",
    buttonStyle.Render("[🔍] fuzzy search"),
)
```

## Example Customizations

### 1. Change Button Emojis

```go
// More modern icons
buttonStyle.Render("[🏡] home"),      // house emoji
buttonStyle.Render("[⭐] favs"),       // shorter label
buttonStyle.Render("[$] shell"),      // dollar sign for command
buttonStyle.Render("[🔎] find"),       // magnifying glass
```

### 2. Add New Buttons

```go
// Add a help button
toolbar := lipgloss.JoinHorizontal(
    lipgloss.Top,
    buttonStyle.Render("[🏠] home"),
    " ",
    favoriteButton,
    " ",
    buttonStyle.Render("[>_] command"),
    " ",
    buttonStyle.Render("[🔍] search"),
    " ",
    buttonStyle.Render("[❓] help"),    // NEW!
)
```

Note: You'll also need to add mouse click handling in `update_mouse.go` for new buttons.

### 3. Minimalist Style

```go
// Text-only, no boxes
lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color("39")).Render("🏠 home"),
" | ",
favoriteButton,
" | ",
lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color("39")).Render(">_ cmd"),
```

### 4. Nerd Font Icons (if available)

```go
// Use Nerd Font icons instead of emoji
buttonStyle.Render("[ ] home"),      //
buttonStyle.Render("[ ] favs"),      //
buttonStyle.Render("[ ] term"),      //
buttonStyle.Render("[ ] find"),      //
```

## Color Customization

Change button colors by modifying `buttonStyle` (around line 70):

```go
// Default (cyan)
buttonStyle := lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color("39"))

// Green theme
buttonStyle := lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color("76"))

// Orange theme
buttonStyle := lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color("208"))

// Purple theme
buttonStyle := lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color("141"))
```

## Adding Click Handlers

If you add new buttons, update `update_mouse.go` (around line 160):

```go
// Example: Add click handler for help button at position X
if mouseX >= helpButtonStart && mouseX <= helpButtonEnd {
    // Open help
    return m, tea.Batch(tea.ClearScreen, openHelp())
}
```

## Files Modified

- `view.go` (toolbar rendering)
- `update_mouse.go` (click handlers, if adding new buttons)

Rebuild after changes: `go build -o tfe`

## Tips

- Keep labels short (5-10 chars) to fit narrow terminals
- Test on 80-column terminal to ensure everything fits
- Emoji can render differently across terminals/fonts
- Consistent spacing: use " " between buttons
